on-deterministic. Agentic level is required because LLM inference latency is both the dominant component and non-deterministic—it varies across runs and depends on model load, input complexity, and sampling strategy. Without real LLM calls, latency tests are useless.","test_description":"Execute 30+ realistic product queries end-to-end using the real embedding API, vector database, and LLM re-ranker in sequence, measure total latency from query input to ranked results returned, and assert that the 50th percentile (median) latency is below 2 seconds","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Agentic test requires real LLM inference, which is the primary latency contributor and is non-deterministic. System-level test with mocked LLM would not catch actual LLM latency failures.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.35,"Agentic":0.6,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13400,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13400},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a27dea2-3871-48dd-a8b7-99ab8dc73880","uuid":"dfc717e6-b215-48d6-9ceb-bda001ecd4de"}
